This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to understand the meaning of words used by web-users to describe objects in a language game. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses soft constraints to model the meaning of descriptions, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with image recognition and context analysis, which are relevant topics in Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques to extract the syntax and words' classes used in the descriptions, which is a sub-topic of Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
